Over R1 billion has been set aside to assist the taxi industry. This was announced by Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula. Aviwe Mtila has more #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The heavy backlog in the issuing of car licenses is being blamed on a malfunctioning machine which had to be sent to Germany for repairs. Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says he will be announcing temporary measures shortly. READ: Grace period for driver's licence renewal extended "The license machine is in Germany, it has broken," Mbalula said. "I am going to be announcing temporary measures with regards to temporary license but I am moving ahead with the new driver's license cards which I will announce in public."